


copfac(1)                      Scilab Function                      copfac(1)






NAME
  copfac - right coprime factorization

CALLING SEQUENCE
  [N,M,XT,YT]=copfac(G [,polf,polc,tol])

PARAMETERS

  G           : syslin list  (continuous-time linear system )

  polf, polc  : respectively the poles of XT and YT and the poles of n and M
              (default values =-1).

  tol         : real threshold for detecting stable poles (default value
              100*%eps)

  N,M,XT,YT   : linear systems represented by syslin lists

DESCRIPTION
  [N,M,XT,YT]=copfac(G,[polf,polc,[tol]]) returns a right coprime factoriza-
  tion of G.

  G = N*M^-1 where N and M are stable, proper and right coprime.  (i.e. [N M]
  left-invertible with stability)

  XT and YT satisfy:

  [XT -YT].[M N]' = eye (Bezout identity)

  G is assumed stabilizable and detectable.

SEE ALSO
  syslin, lcf























